'''森林砍伐'''，或稱'''森林開伐'''、'''去森林化'''（{{lang|en|Deforestation}}）、'''森林破壞'''<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://terms.naer.edu.tw/search/?q=%22deforestation%22&field=ti&op=AND&match=&q=&field=ti&op=AND&order=&num=50&show=&page=&group=&heading=#result |title=Deforestation - 國家教育研究院雙語詞彙、學術名詞暨辭書資訊網 |accessdate=2016-01-04 |archive-date=2016-03-05 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160305095900/http://terms.naer.edu.tw/search/?q=%22deforestation%22&field=ti&op=AND&match=&q=&field=ti&op=AND&order=&num=50&show=&page=&group=&heading=#result |dead-url=no }}</ref>，意為人為的將[[森林|森林]]地轉成[[耕地|耕地]]、[[牧場|牧場]]、[[城市|城市]]等用地的行為。一般來說，森林開伐會造成[[環境退化|環境退化]]和[[物種多樣性|物種多樣性]]的減少。許多國家還在進行森林開伐，造成了[[氣候變遷|氣候變遷]]和地理環境的改變。因為森林砍伐後沒有足夠的[[造林|造林]]，結果破壞水土、氣候變遷、物種多樣性減少和生活品質的下降。<ref>http://www.actionbioscience.org/environment/nilsson.html {{Wayback|url=http://www.actionbioscience.org/environment/nilsson.html |date=20190607205907 }} Do We Have Enough Forests?
By Sten Nilsson</ref>

自19世紀中期，約在1852年之後，地球已經經歷了前所未有的森林破壞<ref name="Wilson">E.O. Wilson, 2002, ''The Future of Life'', Vintage ISBN 0-679-76811-4</ref>。[[歐洲|歐洲]]的森林正在被[[酸雨|酸雨]]侵蝕，而[[西伯利亞|西伯利亞]]的森林非常大的地區自從[[蘇聯瓦解|蘇聯瓦解]]之後就被轉成[[耕地|耕地]]。在過去20年，[[阿富汗|阿富汗]]已經失去了超過70%的森林<ref>[http://www.yubanet.com/artman/publish/article_62235.shtml Afghanistan: Environmental crisis looms as conflict goes on] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20080616214414/http://www.yubanet.com/artman/publish/article_62235.shtml |date=2008-06-16 }}</ref>然而全世界的[[熱帶雨林|熱帶雨林]]破壞所造成的影響最為突出，像是[[物種多樣性|物種多樣性]]和正在進行中的[[全新世滅絕事件|全新世大滅絕]]。<ref>Leakey, Richard and Roger Lewin, 1996, ''The Sixth Extinction : Patterns of Life and the Future of Humankind'', Anchor, ISBN 0-385-46809-1</ref>根据[[联合国粮农组织|联合国粮农组织]]的报告，全球森林面积正以每年减少730万公顷的速度消失。而目前，非法采伐已经成为森林消失的主要原因。

沒做充足的[[林地復育|林地復育]]就砍伐樹木，將[[棲息地破壞|破壞棲息地]]、喪失生物多樣性、造成乾旱。觀察目前狀況和過去[[化石|化石]]記錄就能發現，森林砍伐造成了物種[[滅絕|滅絕]]、氣候條件改變、[[沙漠化|沙漠化]]、人們流離失所<ref name=":4">{{Cite web|title=Rainforest collapse triggered Carboniferous tetrapod diversification in Euramerica|url=https://pubs.geoscienceworld.org/gsa/geology/article-abstract/38/12/1079/130093/Rainforest-collapse-triggered-Carboniferous?redirectedFrom=fulltext|access-date=202205-25|author=S. Sahney ; M. J. Benton  & H. J. Falcon-Lang|date=2010-12-01|publisher=Geology|language=en}}</ref>，森林砍伐也會減少大氣二氧化碳裡的生物性碳封存（biosequestration）當量，增強負循環導致全球暖化。<ref>{{Cite web|title=非洲森林覆蓋率逐步下降，人類毀林行為正在加劇氣候危機！|url=https://www.greenpeace.org/taiwan/update/27628/%E9%9D%9E%E6%B4%B2%E6%A3%AE%E6%9E%97%E8%A6%86%E8%93%8B%E7%8E%87%E9%80%90%E6%AD%A5%E4%B8%8B%E9%99%8D%EF%BC%8C%E4%BA%BA%E9%A1%9E%E6%AF%80%E6%9E%97%E8%A1%8C%E7%82%BA%E6%AD%A3%E5%9C%A8%E5%8A%A0%E5%8A%87/|access-date=2022-05-25|date=2021-10-13|publisher=綠色和平}}</ref>全球暖化又反過來造成那些為了[[粮食安全|食物無虞]]而砍伐森林發展農業的居民們更大壓力，全面地導致耕地減少。通常這些區域都難免產生嚴重的環境問題，例如過度的[[土壤侵蝕|土壤侵蝕]]和退化成荒地。<ref>{{Cite web|title=濫伐森林、過度放牧 南美上億頃土地劣化|url=https://e-info.org.tw/node/116473|access-date=2022-05-25|author=姜唯、蔡麗伶|date=2016-06-21|publisher=環境資訊中心}}</ref>

人類糧食系統的復原能量及適應未來變化的能力都與生物多樣性息息相關—例如耐旱灌木和樹種有助於防治荒漠化、森林裡棲息的昆蟲、蝙蝠和鳥類可以替農作物授粉、山地生態系的樹木因扎根深廣可以防止水土流失、沿海地區的[[红树林|紅樹林]]可以緩衝洪水氾濫。 由於氣候變化讓糧食系統面臨更大的風險，森林具有的碳捕捉儲存及氣候緩解作用，對農業就愈形重要。<ref name=":5">{{Cite web|title=The State of the World’s Forests 2020. In brief|url=https://www.fao.org/documents/card/en/c/ca8985en|access-date=2022-05-25|author=FAO & UNEP|date=2020|publisher=FAO & UNEP|language=en}}</ref>

== 森林的定義 ==
要定義什麼是森林並不容易，因為森林型態包羅萬象，緯度、溫度、降雨模式、土壤成分和人類活動等都是相關因素。除了具體因素之外，定義往往取決於誰在下定義。生活在不同區域的人可能會以截然不同的方式來認定森林；商人、經濟學家、林務員、農民或鳥類學家各自的評估與定義也天差地別。研究發現世上還在使用的森林定義超過800種，在不同領域出於不同目的就會有不同定義。用植物物理特徵（例如樹冠）來進行定義，最有可能用來評估森林範圍；用植物的生物學特性則適合用來區分不同類型的森林。<ref name=":6">{{Cite book|title=Vital Forest Graphics|publisher=UNEP；FAO；UNFF|year=2009|isbn=978-92-5-106264-7|url=https://www.unep.org/resources/report/vital-forest-graphics}}</ref>{{Rp|6}}

[[联合国粮食及农业组织|聯合國糧食及農業組織]]（FAO）使用的森林定義為：樹木高度最少5米、樹冠在地面上產生密集陰影所覆蓋的區域達10%以及森林面積至少有0.5公頃。因此城市公園、果園和其他農作物都不算森林。根據這個定義，目前全球只有40億公頃的森林，覆蓋約30%的陸地面積。FAO 2009年的定義雖然區分了開放和封閉森林（樹冠覆蓋率達40%以上），卻沒有區分原始森林、次生林、退化林地、病害森林和人造森林等複雜情況，影響到森林砍伐的評估。<ref name=":6" />{{Rp|7, 9}} 到了2020年，FAO沿用前述定義，還在森林覆蓋土地之外，納入樹木覆蓋土地（包含城市中的樹木、果園、棕梠、混合林等），並針對森林特徵區分出天然林（細分為原始林和次生林）和人工林（細分為人工造林和其他人工林）。<ref name=":7" />{{RP|11-15}}

[[联合国气候变化框架公约|聯合國氣候變化綱要公約]]（UNFCCC）的定義略有不同，它要求各國自行用其定義來估算森林面積，並記錄在該國溫室氣體清單報告中。<ref name=":6" />{{Rp|7-8}}從《[[京都议定书|京都議定書》]]之補充報告看來，工業國家的森林定義閾值為：成熟樹木高度最少2～5米、樹冠覆蓋區達10～30%以及森林面積最少達0.01-1.0公頃。<ref>{{Cite book|title=2013 Revised Supplementary Methods and Good Practice Guidance Arising from the Kyoto Protocol|publisher=IPCC|year=2014|isbn=978-92-9169-140-1|location=Switzerland|pages=20|url=https://www.ipcc.ch/site/assets/uploads/2018/03/KP_Supplement_Entire_Report.pdf}}</ref>

[[联合国环境署|聯合國環境署]]（UNEP）的定義標準也不同，例如樹冠覆蓋區域最少要達40%。並用遙感技術來測量跨國家的森林區。根據UNEP評估，1995年全球約有28.7億公頃封閉森林，佔全球陸地面積21.4%。<ref name=":6" />{{Rp|8-9}}

森林砍伐及森林退化是不同的概念。森林砍伐指的是徹底及永久地消除森林區域，直接造成森林覆蓋面積的減少，換言之，如果能連續地維持森林覆蓋率（例如以森林管理為優先目標所遂行的森林利用），就不構成森林砍伐。另一方面，森林退化則不涉及森林面積的減少，而著重在森林狀況的質量下降，例如生物多樣性減少、森林結構遭破壞及功能不完整。<ref name="Lanly">Lanly, Jean-Paul. [http://www.fao.org/docrep/article/wfc/xii/ms12a-e.htm "Deforestation and Forest Degradation Factors"]. In: ''XII World Forestry Congress'', Québec, 2003</ref><ref name=":7">{{Cite book|title=2020年世界森林狀況|publisher=聯合國糧食及農業組織|year=2020|isbn=978-92-5-132424-0|pages=|url=https://www.fao.org/publications/sofo/2022/zh/}}</ref>{{RP|xvi-xvii}}

== 歷史背景（1970年起） ==
[[File:Operação_Hymenaea,_Julho-2016_(29399454651).jpg|缩略图]]]]
聯合國糧食及農業組織估計1990年至2020年間，全球森林碳儲量下降0.9%，樹木覆蓋率下降 4.2%。<ref name=":0">{{Cite book|title=Global Forest Resources Assessment 2020|publisher=[[FAO|FAO]]|year=2021|isbn=978-92-5-134155-1|location=Rome, Italy|pages=|url=https://www.fao.org/3/ca9825en/CA9825EN.pdf}}</ref>{{Rp|16, 52}}<ref>{{Cite web|title=2020年全球森林資源評估|url=https://www.fao.org/forest-resources-assessment/2020/zh|access-date=2022-05-26|author=糧農組織|date=2021|publisher=FAO}}</ref>同期的歐洲（包括俄羅斯）森林碳儲量從158.7 Gt（千兆噸）增加到172.4 Gt。北美洲從136.6 Gt增加到140 Gt。而非洲卻從94.3 Gt下降到80.9 Gt，南亞及東南亞從45.8 Gt下降到41.5 Gt，大洋洲從33.4 Gt下降到33.1 Gt，中美洲從5 Gt下降到4.1 Gt，南美洲從161.8 Gt下降到144.8 Gt。<ref name=":0" />{{Rp|52}}[[政府間氣候變化專門委員會|政府間氣候變化專門委員會]]（IPCC）表示對於全球森林是否正在萎縮的意見不一，並引用研究報告《[https://www.ipcc.ch/srccl/ 氣候變化和土地]》說明1982年至2016年間樹木覆蓋率增加了7.1%<ref name=":1">{{Cite book|title=Climate Change and Land: an IPCC special report on climate change, desertification, land degradation, sustainable land management, food security, and greenhouse gas fluxes in terrestrial ecosystems.|publisher=[[IPCC|IPCC]]|year=2019|url=https://www.ipcc.ch/site/assets/uploads/sites/4/2019/11/07_Chapter-4.pdf|chapter=Ch4. Land Degradation}}</ref>{{Rp|367}}，雖然熱帶地區的地上生物碳儲量下降，但是溫帶和北方森林的碳儲量都增加，所以全球碳儲量為正成長。<ref name=":1" />{{Rp|385}}

導致森林遭全面砍伐或零碎開墾並連帶影響森林生物多樣性喪失，主因依舊是農業開發。2000年至2010年間，40%熱帶森林開墾被用來進行大規模貿易農業（養牛、種植大豆及[[油棕|油棕]]為主），而當地自給農業佔33%。<ref name=":2">{{Cite book|title=The State of the World’s Forests 2020. In brief|last=FAO & UNEP|publisher=FAO & UNEP|year=2020|isbn=978-92-5-132707-4|location=Rome, Italy|url=https://www.fao.org/documents/card/en/c/ca8985en}}</ref>{{Rp|10-11}}砍下樹木可當成建材、[[木料|木料]]或燃料（[[木炭|木炭]]或木柴），清空土地則用作牧場或農場。絕大多數伐林以遂行之農業活動還享有政府[[農業補貼|農業補貼]]。<ref>{{Cite web|title=Government Subsidies for Agriculture May Exacerbate Deforestation, says new UN report|url=https://www.un.org/sustainabledevelopment/blog/2015/09/government-subsidies-for-agriculture-may-exacerbate-deforestation-says-new-un-report/|access-date=2022-05-27|date=2015-09-03|publisher=UN|language=en}}</ref>忽視森林附加價值、管理疏忽和環境法規不完備都是導致大規模毀林的因素。無論是自然發生<ref>{{Cite web|title=The causes of deforestation|url=https://www.eniscuola.net/en/argomento/rain-forest/deforestation/the-causes-of-deforestation/|access-date=2022-05-27|publisher=Eniscuola|language=en}}</ref>或人為造成，毀林都是許多國家長期存在的問題。<ref>{{Cite web|title=The five: areas of deforestation|url=https://www.theguardian.com/environment/2019/nov/24/the-five-areas-of-deforestation-amazon-ethiopia-siberia-papua-south-sudan|access-date=2022-05-27|author=Gregory Robinson|date=2019-11-24|publisher=The Guardian|language=en}}</ref>2000年至2012年間，全球有230萬平方公里的森林被砍伐<ref>{{Cite web|title=Rainforests|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20151022034531/http://www.nature.org/ourinitiatives/urgentissues/rainforests/rainforests-facts.xml|access-date=2022-05-27|publisher=The Nature Conservancy|language=en}}</ref>，而持續毀林及林地退化的速度驚人，不斷加劇生物多樣性的喪失。<ref name=":2" />{{Rp|12-14}}
[[File:Land-use-of-different-diets-Poore-Nemecek.png|缩略图]]
新興國家對於熱帶和亞熱帶森林的砍伐更劇烈。<ref name="Rainforest Facts">[http://www.nature.org/ourinitiatives/urgentissues/rainforests/rainforests-facts.xml Rainforest Facts] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20151022034531/http://www.nature.org/ourinitiatives/urgentissues/rainforests/rainforests-facts.xml|date=22 October 2015}}. Nature.org (1 November 2016). Retrieved 13 November 2016.</ref>熱帶雨林孕育了世界上超過一半的陸地動物與植物物種。地球上原有1,600萬平方公里的熱帶雨林，在大量砍伐後只剩下620萬平方公里（減少61%）。<ref name="nature1">[http://www.nature.org/ourinitiatives/urgentissues/rainforests/rainforests-facts.xml "Facts About Rainforests"] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20151022034531/http://www.nature.org/ourinitiatives/urgentissues/rainforests/rainforests-facts.xml|date=22 October 2015}}. [[The_Nature_Conservancy|The Nature Conservancy]]. Retrieved 19 October 2015.</ref>亞馬遜雨林中每分鐘都有一個[[足球場|足球場]]大小的區域被清空，面積總計約5,500萬公頃，多數用於畜牧業。<ref>{{cite web|title=Amazon Destruction|url=https://rainforests.mongabay.com/amazon/amazon_destruction.html|access-date=13 December 2017|website=Mongabay}}</ref>光2018年就有超過360萬公頃的原始熱帶雨林消失，主因是為了生產牛肉供消費，<ref>[https://www.theguardian.com/environment/2019/may/06/human-society-under-urgent-threat-loss-earth-natural-life-un-report Human society under urgent threat from loss of Earth's natural life. Scientists reveal 1 million species at risk of extinction in damning UN report] 6 May 2019 Guardian [https://www.dropbox.com/sh/yd8l2v0u4jqptp3/AACpraYjOYWpTxAFv5H-2vrKa/1%20Global%20Assessment%20Summary%20for%20Policymakers?dl=0&preview=Summary+for+Policymakers+IPBES+Global+Assessment.pdf&subfolder_nav_tracking=1]</ref>大約80%的土地開發都是為了飼養牛隻。<ref>{{cite news|last=Wang|first=George C.|date=9 April 2017|title=Go vegan, save the planet|work=[[CNN|CNN]]|url=http://www.cnn.com/2017/04/08/opinions/go-vegan-save-the-planet-wang/|access-date=25 August 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last=Liotta|first=Edoardo|date=23 August 2019|title=Feeling Sad About the Amazon Fires? Stop Eating Meat|work=[[Vice_Media|Vice]]|url=https://www.vice.com/en_in/article/bjwzk4/feeling-sad-about-the-amazon-fires-stop-eating-meat|access-date=25 August 2019}}</ref>自1970年以來，被砍伐的亞馬遜雨林土地91%都成為養牛場。<ref name="fao">{{cite book|author1=Steinfeld, Henning|url=http://www.fao.org/docrep/010/a0701e/a0701e00.htm|title=Livestock's Long Shadow: Environmental Issues and Options|author2=Gerber, Pierre|author3=Wassenaar, T. D.|author4=Castel, Vincent|publisher=[[Food_and_Agriculture_Organization_of_the_United_Nations|Food and Agriculture Organization of the United Nations]]|year=2006|isbn=978-92-5-105571-7|access-date=19 August 2008}}</ref><ref>{{cite book|last=Margulis|first=Sergio|url=http://www-wds.worldbank.org/servlet/WDSContentServer/WDSP/IB/2004/02/02/000090341_20040202130625/Rendered/PDF/277150PAPER0wbwp0no1022.pdf|title=Causes of Deforestation of the Brazilian Amazon|work=World Bank Working Paper No. 22|publisher=The World Bank|year=2004|isbn=0-8213-5691-7|location=Washington D.C.|page=9|access-date=4 September 2008|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20080910042549/http://www-wds.worldbank.org/servlet/WDSContentServer/WDSP/IB/2004/02/02/000090341_20040202130625/Rendered/PDF/277150PAPER0wbwp0no1022.pdf|archive-date=10 September 2008|url-status=live}}</ref>全球每年樹木淨減量估計約為100億棵。<ref>{{cite news|date=2 September 2015|title=Earth has 3 trillion trees but they're falling at alarming rate|language=en|work=Reuters|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-science-trees-idUSKCN0R21Z620150902|access-date=26 May 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Tree planting 'has mind-blowing potential' to tackle climate crisis|url=https://www.theguardian.com/environment/2019/jul/04/planting-billions-trees-best-tackle-climate-crisis-scientists-canopy-emissions|access-date=26 May 2020|date=4 July 2019|website=The Guardian|last1=Carrington|first1=Damian}}</ref>根據《[https://www.fao.org/3/ca9825en/ca9825en.pdf 2020年全球森林資源評估]》，2000-2010年間森林面積年平均淨損失為470萬公頃，2015-2020年間，全球年平均森林砍伐面積為1,000萬公頃。自1990年算起，地球已經失去了1.78億公頃森林，相當於[[利比亚|利比亞]]國土面積。<ref name=":0" />{{Rp|XI-XII}}

2020年《[[科學報告|科學報告]]》上的研究指出，如果以目前速度繼續砍伐森林，可能會在未來20至40 年內造成[[人類滅絕|人類完全滅絕]]。報告結論是：就統計角度看來......在最樂觀的情況下，人類文明存續的機率不到10%。為了避免文明崩壞，人類應該從「經濟導向的生活方式」轉型成「文化社會」，即生態系統的整體利益優先於系統組成分子的個別利益，最終方能符合全體的公共利益。<ref>{{cite web|title=Theoretical Physicists Say 90% Chance of Societal Collapse Within Several Decades|url=https://www.vice.com/en_us/article/akzn5a/theoretical-physicists-say-90-chance-of-societal-collapse-within-several-decades|access-date=9 August 2020|website=Vice|last1=Nafeez|first1=Ahmed}}</ref><ref>{{cite journal |last1=Bologna |first1=M. |last2=Aquino |first2=G. |date=2020 |title=Deforestation and world population sustainability: a quantitative analysis |url= |journal=Scientific Reports |volume=10 |issue=7631 |page=7631 |arxiv=2006.12202 |bibcode=2020NatSR..10.7631B |doi=10.1038/s41598-020-63657-6 |pmc=7203172 |pmid=32376879}}</ref>

37個國家與150多個團體組織於2014年簽署《紐約森林宣言》，自願承諾2020年前將森林砍伐率減半，2030年要停止所有砍伐。但是該協議不具法律約束力，而且巴西、中國和俄羅斯等關鍵國家都沒有簽署，事後看來《紐約森林宣言》以失敗告終，2014年到2020年森林砍伐不只沒減少反倒增加。<ref>{{cite news|title=COP26: World leaders promise to end deforestation by 2030|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/science-environment-59088498|work=BBC News|date=2 November 2021}}</ref><ref name="Butlerb">{{cite news|author=Rhett A. Butler|url=https://news.mongabay.com/2021/11/glasgow-declaration-what-countries-are-leaders-in-reducing-deforestation/|title=What countries are leaders in reducing deforestation? Which are not?|date=5 November 2021|publisher=Mongabay}}</ref>2021年11月，141個國家（佔了全球約85%的原始熱帶雨林和90%森林覆蓋率）在COP26氣候峰會上簽署《格拉斯哥森林與土地利用領袖宣言》，承諾在2030年前停止森林砍伐並把樹木種回來，<ref name="Butlerb" /><ref name="SpringJessop">{{cite news|authors=Jake Spring & Simon Jessop|title=Over 100 global leaders pledge to end deforestation by 2030|url=https://www.reuters.com/business/environment/over-100-global-leaders-pledge-end-deforestation-by-2030-2021-11-01/|work=Reuters|date=3 November 2021}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://ukcop26.org/glasgow-leaders-declaration-on-forests-and-land-use/1|title=Glasgow Leaders' Declaration on Forests and Land Use|publisher=[[2021_United_Nations_Climate_Change_Conference|2021 United Nations Climate Change Conference]]|date=November 12, 2021}}</ref>還答應投入約192億美元的資金。<ref>{{Cite web|title=【COP26直擊】森林、甲烷、五大行業 百國領導人簽署三大協議 強生說：拆彈小組開始剪斷線路，為1.5°C努力|url=https://csr.cw.com.tw/article/42234|access-date=2020-05-29|author=王茜穎|date=2021-11-03|publisher=CSR＠天下}}</ref><ref name="SpringJessop2">{{cite news|authors=Jake Spring & Simon Jessop|title=Over 100 global leaders pledge to end deforestation by 2030|url=https://www.reuters.com/business/environment/over-100-global-leaders-pledge-end-deforestation-by-2030-2021-11-01/|work=Reuters|date=3 November 2021}}</ref>相較於《紐約森林宣言》，2021年的宣言增加了巴西和許多其他先前未簽署的國家，<ref name="Butlerb" /><ref name="SpringJessop5" />但有些森林砍伐率高的指標國家（包括馬來西亞、柬埔寨、寮國、巴拉圭和緬甸）還是沒有簽署。<ref name="SpringJessop5" />加上《格拉斯哥森林與土地利用領袖宣言》是在聯合國氣候變化綱要公約的架構外簽訂的，因此和《紐約森林宣言》一樣不具法律約束力。<ref name="SpringJessop5">{{cite news|authors=Jake Spring & Simon Jessop|title=Over 100 global leaders pledge to end deforestation by 2030|url=https://www.reuters.com/business/environment/over-100-global-leaders-pledge-end-deforestation-by-2030-2021-11-01/|work=[[Reuters|Reuters]]|date=3 November 2021}}</ref>2021年11月，[[欧洲联盟委员会|歐盟執行委員會]]擬定一項法律草案，要求企業證明銷往歐盟4.5億消費者的農產品與森林砍伐無關，包括牛肉、木材、棕櫚油、大豆、咖啡和可可。<ref>{{Cite web|title=EU aims to curb deforestation with beef and coffee import ban|url=https://www.theguardian.com/environment/2021/nov/17/eu-deforestation-beef-coffee-import-ban-commodities-endangered-forests|access-date=2021-11-17|date=2021-11-17|last=Rankin|first=Jennifer|website=The Guardian|language=en|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211117131641/https://www.theguardian.com/environment/2021/nov/17/eu-deforestation-beef-coffee-import-ban-commodities-endangered-forests|archive-date=17 November 2021|url-status=live}}</ref>

== 原因 ==
[[File:Drivers_of_deforestation_and_forest_degradation_by_region,_2000–2010.svg|缩略图]]
聯合國氣候變化綱要公約[[联合国秘书处|秘書處]]說森林砍伐最具壓倒性的直接原因就是農業。森林砍伐中[[自給農業|自給農業]]佔了48%、貿易農業佔32%、[[伐木|伐木]]佔14%、薪柴佔5%。<ref>{{cite web|title=Investment and financial flows to address climate change|url=http://unfccc.int/files/essential_background/background_publications_htmlpdf/application/pdf/pub_07_financial_flows.pdf|year=2007|work=unfccc.int|publisher=UNFCCC|page=81}}</ref>
[[File:Drivers_of_tropical_deforestration.png|缩略图]]
到底為了產業而伐木是不是全球森林破壞的重要因素，專家們則無共識。<ref name="causesof">{{cite journal |author1=Angelsen, Arild |author2=Kaimowitz, David |date=February 1999 |title=Rethinking the causes of deforestation: Lessons from economic models |url=https://ideas.repec.org/a/oup/wbrobs/v14y1999i1p73-98.html |journal=The World Bank Research Observer |publisher=Oxford University Press |volume=14 |issue=1 |pages=73–98 |doi=10.1093/wbro/14.1.73 |jstor=3986539 |pmid=12322119}}</ref><ref>{{cite journal |last=Laurance |first=William F. |date=December 1999 |title=Reflections on the tropical deforestation crisis |url=http://studentresearch.wcp.muohio.edu/BiogeogDiversityDisturbance/ReflectionsDeforestCrisis.pdf |url-status=dead |journal=Biological Conservation |volume=91 |issue=2–3 |pages=109–117 |doi=10.1016/S0006-3207(99)00088-9 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20060908032336/http://studentresearch.wcp.muohio.edu/BiogeogDiversityDisturbance/ReflectionsDeforestCrisis.pdf |archive-date=8 September 2006}}</ref>有人認為窮人更可能砍伐森林，因為他們別無選擇；有人認為富人才是元兇，因為窮人沒有能力支付伐林所需的人力物力。<ref name="causesof2">{{cite journal |author1=Angelsen, Arild |author2=Kaimowitz, David |date=February 1999 |title=Rethinking the causes of deforestation: Lessons from economic models |url=https://ideas.repec.org/a/oup/wbrobs/v14y1999i1p73-98.html |journal=The World Bank Research Observer |publisher=Oxford University Press |volume=14 |issue=1 |pages=73–98 |doi=10.1093/wbro/14.1.73 |jstor=3986539 |pmid=12322119}}</ref>研究發現，當地高生育率導致人口增加只佔熱帶森林砍伐主因8%。<ref>{{cite journal |last1=Geist |first1=Helmut J. |last2=Lambin |first2=Eric F. |date=February 2002 |title=Proximate Causes and Underlying Driving Forces of Tropical Deforestation |journal=BioScience |volume=52 |issue=2 |pages=143–150 |doi=10.1641/0006-3568(2002)052[0143:PCAUDF]2.0.CO;2 |doi-access=free}}</ref>

現今森林砍伐的原因可能還有政府機構的貪瀆<ref>{{cite news|url=http://newsinfo.inquirer.net/breakingnews/nation/view_article.php?article_id=110193|title=Corruption blamed for deforestation|first=T.J.|last=Burgonio|newspaper=Philippine Daily Inquirer|date=3 January 2008}}{{Dead link|date=November 2018|bot=InternetArchiveBot|fix-attempted=yes}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=WRM Bulletin Number 74|url=http://www.wrm.org.uy/bulletin/74/Uganda.html|access-date=17 October 2008|date=September 2003|publisher=World Rainforest Movement|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20081004225352/http://www.wrm.org.uy/bulletin/74/Uganda.html|archive-date=4 October 2008|url-status=dead}}</ref>、不公平的財富及權力分配<ref>{{cite web|title=Global Deforestation|url=http://www.globalchange.umich.edu/globalchange2/current/lectures/deforest/deforest.html|date=4 January 2006|work=Global Change Curriculum|publisher=University of Michigan Global Change Program|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110615044847/http://www.globalchange.umich.edu/globalchange2/current/lectures/deforest/deforest.html|archive-date=15 June 2011|url-status=dead}}</ref>、人口成長<ref name="population1">{{cite web|title=Population and deforestation|url=http://www.fao.org/sd/WPdirect/WPan0050.htm|author=Marcoux, Alain|date=August 2000|work=SD Dimensions|publisher=Sustainable Development Department, Food and Agriculture Organization of the United Nations (FAO)|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110628184520/http://www.fao.org/sd/WPdirect/WPan0050.htm|archive-date=28 June 2011|url-status=dead}}</ref>與[[人口過多|過多]]<ref>{{cite web|title=Impact of Population and Poverty on Rainforests|url=http://rainforests.mongabay.com/0816.htm|access-date=13 May 2009|last=Butler|first=Rhett A|work=Mongabay.com / A Place Out of Time: Tropical Rainforests and the Perils They Face}}</ref><ref name="r12">{{cite web|title=The Choice: Doomsday or Arbor Day|url=http://www.umich.edu/~gs265/society/deforestation.htm|work=umich.edu|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090416161300/http://www.umich.edu/~gs265/society/deforestation.htm|archive-date=16 April 2009|author1=Stock, Jocelyn|author2=Rochen, Andy|url-status=dead}}</ref>、[[城市化|都市化]]<ref>{{cite web|title=Demographics, Democracy, Development, Disparity and Deforestation: A Crossnational Assessment of the Social Causes of Deforestation|url=http://www.allacademic.com/meta/p_mla_apa_research_citation/1/0/7/4/8/p107488_index.html|access-date=13 May 2009|author=Ehrhardt-Martinez, Karen|work=Paper presented at the annual meeting of the American Sociological Association, Atlanta Hilton Hotel, Atlanta, GA, 16 August 2003|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20081210160729/http://www.allacademic.com/meta/p_mla_apa_research_citation/1/0/7/4/8/p107488_index.html|archive-date=10 December 2008|url-status=dead}}</ref>。[[全球化|全球化]]常被當成森林砍伐的根本原因，<ref>{{cite web|title=The Double Edge of Globalization|url=http://yaleglobal.yale.edu/display.article?id=9366|date=June 2007|work=YaleGlobal Online|publisher=Yale University Press}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Human Threats to Rainforests—Economic Restructuring|url=http://rainforests.mongabay.com/0805.htm|access-date=13 May 2009|last=Butler|first=Rhett A|work=Mongabay.com / A Place Out of Time: Tropical Rainforests and the Perils They Face}}</ref>不過全球化新注入的勞動力、資本、商品和觀念有時也促進了當地的森林復原。<ref>{{cite journal |last1=Hecht |first1=Susanna B. |last2=Kandel |first2=Susan |last3=Gomes |first3=Ileana |last4=Cuellar |first4=Nelson |last5=Rosa |first5=Herman |year=2006 |title=Globalization, Forest Resurgence, and Environmental Politics in El Salvador |url=http://www.spa.ucla.edu/cgpr/docs/sdarticle1.pdf |url-status=dead |journal=World Development |volume=34 |issue=2 |pages=308–323 |doi=10.1016/j.worlddev.2005.09.005 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20081029090622/http://www.spa.ucla.edu/cgpr/docs/sdarticle1.pdf |archive-date=29 October 2008 |access-date=17 October 2008}}</ref>

另一個破壞森林的原因是氣候變化。23%森林面積損失乃森林火災和氣候變化所致，其頻率和規模都在增加。<ref>{{cite journal |last1=Harris |first1=Nancy |last2=Dow Goldman |first2=Elizabeth |last3=Weisse |first3=Mikaela |last4=Barrett |first4=Alyssa |date=13 September 2018 |title=When a Tree Falls, Is It Deforestation? |url=https://www.wri.org/blog/2018/09/when-tree-falls-it-deforestation |access-date=30 August 2019 |website=World Resources Institute}}</ref>氣溫上升導致了大規模野火，尤其是在[[北方針葉林|北方針葉林]]帶，可能是森林結構變化的關係。<ref>{{cite news|last1=Dapcevich|first1=Madison|title=Disastrous Wildfires Sweeping Through Alaska Could Permanently Alter Forest Composition|url=https://www.ecowatch.com/alaska-wildfires-forests-trees-2640081853.html|access-date=30 August 2019|agency=Ecowatch|date=28 August 2019}}</ref>

聯合國糧農組織發現「當地人口增長對於森林破壞來說已經從關鍵因素變成無關緊要」，森林砍伐的原因很可能是「人口壓力加上經濟、社會及科技發展停滯的綜合作用」。<ref name="population12">{{cite web|title=Population and deforestation|url=http://www.fao.org/sd/WPdirect/WPan0050.htm|author=Marcoux, Alain|date=August 2000|work=SD Dimensions|publisher=Sustainable Development Department, Food and Agriculture Organization of the United Nations (FAO)|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110628184520/http://www.fao.org/sd/WPdirect/WPan0050.htm|archive-date=28 June 2011|url-status=dead}}</ref>
[[File:Riau_deforestation_2006.jpg|缩略图]]最後一批被砍伐的木材，此處伐林是為了種植油棕。]]
從經濟激勵措施的角度來看森林生態系統的退化，開發森林似乎比保護森林更有利可圖。<ref name="economicvalue">{{cite journal |last=Pearce |first=David W |date=December 2001 |title=The Economic Value of Forest Ecosystems |url=http://www.cbd.int/doc/external/academic/forest-es-2003-en.pdf |journal=Ecosystem Health |volume=7 |issue=4 |pages=284–296 |doi=10.1046/j.1526-0992.2001.01037.x}}</ref> 森林的許多重要功能沒有市場，對於森林地主或依賴森林維生的居民來說，也就沒有現實的經濟價值。<ref name="economicvalue" />站在開發中國家的角度，森林可儲存碳化合物及孕育生物多樣性的好處幾乎都被已開發國家給佔了，犧牲開發利益換來[[碳匯|碳匯]]及生物多樣性卻沒有得到足夠的補償。除此之外，有些已開發國家（例如美國）在幾世紀前就砍伐了開發中國家的森林並攫取經濟利益，現在卻剝奪他們這樣的機會未免虛偽，換句話說，富人惹麻煩哪能要窮人繳保護費。<ref name="costarica">{{cite journal |last1=Bulte |first1=Erwin H |last2=Joenje |first2=Mark |last3=Jansen |first3=Hans GP |year=2000 |title=Is there too much or too little natural forest in the Atlantic Zone of Costa Rica? |journal=Canadian Journal of Forest Research |volume=30 |issue=3 |pages=495–506 |doi=10.1139/x99-225}}</ref>

有些評論員也注意到過去30年間森林砍伐的驅動因素有所轉變。<ref>{{cite journal |author1=Butler, Rhett A. |author2=Laurance, William F. |date=August 2008 |title=New strategies for conserving tropical forests |url=http://news.mongabay.com/Butler_and_Laurance-TREE.pdf |journal=Trends in Ecology & Evolution |volume=23 |issue=9 |pages=469–472 |doi=10.1016/j.tree.2008.05.006 |pmid=18656280}}</ref>在19世紀末和20世紀初期10年，森林砍伐主要是謀生活動或政府資助發展項目所造成的，例如[[印尼國內移民計劃|印尼國內移民計劃]]和拉丁美洲、印度、爪哇等地的[[殖民|殖民]]；1990年代大部分森林砍伐來自產業因素，包括採掘業、大規模養牛場和粗放農業。<ref name="rud">Rudel, T.K. (2005) [https://books.google.com/books?id=j4AvOb_R9h8C&printsec=frontcover ''Tropical Forests: Regional Paths of Destruction and Regeneration in the Late 20th Century'']. Columbia University Press {{ISBN|0-231-13195-X}}</ref>自2001年以來，商品導向（commodity-driven）因素佔了森林開發活動的四分之一，主要集中在南美洲和東南亞。<ref name="CurtisSlay2018">{{cite journal |last1=Curtis |first1=P. G. |last2=Slay |first2=C. M. |last3=Harris |first3=N. L. |last4=Tyukavina |first4=A. |last5=Hansen |first5=M. C. |year=2018 |title=Classifying drivers of global forest loss |journal=Science |volume=361 |issue=6407 |pages=1108–1111 |bibcode=2018Sci...361.1108C |doi=10.1126/science.aau3445 |pmid=30213911 |s2cid=52273353 |doi-access=free}}</ref>

== 環境影響 ==

=== 大氣 ===
