森林砍伐仍持續發生並影響著氣候和地貌。<ref>{{cite web|title=NASA DATA SHOWS DEFORESTATION AFFECTS CLIMATE|url=http://www.nasa.gov/centers/goddard/news/topstory/2004/0603amazondry.html|date=9 June 2004|work=Nasa}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Massive deforestation threatens food security|url=http://www.newsfromafrica.org/newsfromafrica/articles/art_9607.html|author=Mweninguwe, Raphael|date=15 February 2005|publisher=newsfromafrica.org|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110718105636/http://www.newsfromafrica.org/newsfromafrica/articles/art_9607.html|archive-date=18 July 2011|url-status=dead}}</ref><ref>[https://www.sciencedaily.com/releases/2007/05/070511100918.htm Confirmed: Deforestation Plays Critical Climate Change Role], ScienceDaily, 11 May 2007.</ref><ref>[http://www.scientificamerican.com/article.cfm?id=clearing-forests-may-transform-local-and-global-climate Clearing Forests May Transform Local—and Global—Climate; Researchers are finding that massive deforestation may have a profound, and possibly catastrophic, impact on local weather] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130413213815/http://www.scientificamerican.com/article.cfm?id=clearing-forests-may-transform-local-and-global-climate|date=13 April 2013}}. [[Scientific_American|Scientific American]] (4 March 2013)</ref>

森林砍伐助長了全球暖化<ref>[http://www.fao.org/newsroom/en/news/2006/1000385/index.html Deforestation causes global warming] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090805131750/http://www.fao.org/newsroom/en/news/2006/1000385/index.html|date=5 August 2009}}, [[FAO|FAO]]</ref><ref name="Fearnidel">{{cite journal |last1=Fearnside |first1=Philip M. |last2=Laurance |first2=William F. |year=2004 |title=Tropical Deforestation and Greenhouse-Gas Emissions |journal=Ecological Applications |volume=14 |issue=4 |pages=982 |doi=10.1890/03-5225}}</ref>，也常被當作擴大溫室效應的主因。光是砍伐熱帶雨林就造成全球約20%的溫室氣體排放量。<ref>{{Cite web|title=Deforestation and desertification|url=https://www.fondationchirac.eu/en/deforestation/|website=Fondation Chirac}}</ref>政府間氣候變化專門委員會（IPCC）2007年氣候變化評估報告（第四次評估）指出，集中在熱帶地區的森林砍伐該當佔了三分之一的人為二氧化碳排放總量。<ref name="IPCC deforestation">IPCC Fourth Assessment Report, Working Group I Report "The Physical Science Basis", [http://www.ipcc.ch/pdf/assessment-report/ar4/wg1/ar4-wg1-chapter7.pdf Section 7.3.3.1.5] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110315005004/http://www.ipcc.ch/pdf/assessment-report/ar4/wg1/ar4-wg1-chapter7.pdf|date=15 March 2011}}. p. 527</ref>但是2009年《自然-地球科學》（Nature Geoscience）研究數據顯示，森林砍伐和林地退化導致的二氧化碳排放（不包括[[泥炭沼地|泥炭地]]）僅佔人為二氧化碳排放總量的12%，誤差範圍為6%至17%。<ref>{{Cite journal |last1=Van Der Werf |first1=G. R. |last2=Morton |first2=D. C. |last3=Defries |first3=R. S. |last4=Olivier |first4=J. G. J. |last5=Kasibhatla |first5=P. S. |last6=Jackson |first6=R. B. |last7=Collatz |first7=G. J. |last8=Randerson |first8=J. T. |year=2009 |title=CO<sub>2</sub> emissions from forest loss |journal=Nature Geoscience |volume=2 |issue=11 |pages=737–738 |bibcode=2009NatGe...2..737V |doi=10.1038/ngeo671}}</ref>另一項2022年的研究表示過去20年熱帶森林砍伐造成的年度碳排放量成長一倍且還在增加（2001-2005年為0.97 ±0.16 PgC yr<sup>-1</sup>，2015-2019年平均為1.99 ±0.13 PgC yr<sup>-1</sup>。1 PgC=10<sup>9</sup> 噸C）。<ref>{{cite news|title=Deforestation emissions far higher than previously thought, study finds|url=https://www.theguardian.com/environment/2022/feb/28/deforestation-emissions-far-higher-than-previously-thought-study-finds-aoe|access-date=16 March 2022|work=The Guardian|date=28 February 2022|language=en}}</ref><ref name="10.1038/s41893-022-00854-3">{{cite journal |last1=Feng |first1=Yu |last2=Zeng |first2=Zhenzhong |last3=Searchinger |first3=Timothy D. |last4=Ziegler |first4=Alan D. |last5=Wu |first5=Jie |last6=Wang |first6=Dashan |last7=He |first7=Xinyue |last8=Elsen |first8=Paul R. |last9=Ciais |first9=Philippe |last10=Xu |first10=Rongrong |last11=Guo |first11=Zhilin |date=28 February 2022 |title=Doubling of annual forest carbon loss over the tropics during the early twenty-first century |journal=Nature Sustainability |language=en |pages=1–8 |doi=10.1038/s41893-022-00854-3 |issn=2398-9629 |s2cid=247160560 |last12=Peng |first12=Liqing |last13=Tao |first13=Yiheng |last14=Spracklen |first14=Dominick V. |last15=Holden |first15=Joseph |last16=Liu |first16=Xiaoping |last17=Zheng |first17=Yi |last18=Xu |first18=Peng |last19=Chen |first19=Ji |last20=Jiang |first20=Xin |last21=Song |first21=Xiao-Peng |last22=Lakshmi |first22=Venkataraman |last23=Wood |first23=Eric F. |last24=Zheng |first24=Chunmiao}}</ref>
[[File:Per-capita-co2-food-deforestation_(1).svg|缩略图]]
森林砍伐對於全球暖化的影響似乎無法一概而論，就有評論說北緯50°以北的大規模伐林反而讓全球整體溫度下降，因為清出空地積存更多的雪以及積雪把大部分陽光反射回去都可以降溫；砍伐熱帶雨林會導致暖化也不單單是由於減少森林就減少二氧化碳的吸納能量，熱帶雨林的生物機制（分泌[[气溶胶|氣溶膠]]）及物理效應（[[蒸腾作用|蒸散作用]]）也有助於降溫，所以把碳匯當作核心指標有待商榷。無論如何，保護熱帶雨林有助於降低全球平均氣溫1°C以上。<ref>{{cite news|title=Forests help reduce global warming in more ways than one|url=https://www.sciencenews.org/article/forest-trees-reduce-global-warming-climate-cooling-carbon|access-date=19 April 2022|work=Science News|date=24 March 2022}}</ref><ref name="10.3389/ffgc.2022.756115/full">{{cite journal |last1=Lawrence |first1=Deborah |last2=Coe |first2=Michael |last3=Walker |first3=Wayne |last4=Verchot |first4=Louis |last5=Vandecar |first5=Karen |date=2022 |title=The Unseen Effects of Deforestation: Biophysical Effects on Climate |journal=Frontiers in Forests and Global Change |volume=5 |doi=10.3389/ffgc.2022.756115 |issn=2624-893X |doi-access=free}}</ref>

IPCC指出2010-2019年全球平均碳排量為 10.9 ± 0.9 PgC yr<sup>-1</sup>，46%累積在大氣中、23%由海洋吸收、31% 儲存在陸地植被中。燃燒化石燃料佔人為二氧化碳排放總量的81-91%，其餘來自土地利用。揭櫫了全球碳排及生物地球化學循環間的複雜反饋關係。<ref>{{Cite book|title=《氣候變化2021：物理科學基礎》|last=IPCC第六次評估—第一工作組|publisher=IPCC|year=2021|pages=676, 699|url=https://www.ipcc.ch/report/ar6/wg1/downloads/report/IPCC_AR6_WGI_Chapter05.pdf}}</ref>雖然1990年以來，二氧化碳年排放量沒有明顯增加趨勢<ref name=":3">{{Cite book|title=《氣候變化和土地—決策者摘要》|publisher=IPCC|year=2019|url=https://www.ipcc.ch/site/assets/uploads/sites/4/2020/06/SRCCL_SPM_zh.pdf}}</ref>{{Rp|10}}，減少毀林和森林退化仍是降低溫室氣體排放的好方法（每年可減少0.4–5.8 GtCO2）；採取永續森林管理模式可以提供木材、纖維質及生態系統帶來的好處，也可以降低溫室氣體排放，有助於氣候適應。<ref name=":3" />{{Rp|23}}

==== 作用方式 ====
[[File:Spatial_pattern_of_forest_carbon_loss_across_the_tropics.webp|缩略图]]
森林砍伐使二氧化碳滯留在[[空气|大氣]]中。二氧化碳持續累積就變成了吸收太陽輻射的氣層。太陽輻射轉化成熱能而導致全球變暖，就是眾所周知的[[温室效应|溫室效應]]。<ref>Mumoki, Fiona (18 July 2006). [https://www.tigweb.org/youth-media/panorama/article.html?ContentID=7611 "The Effects of Deforestation on our Environment Today".] Panorama. TakingITGlobal..</ref>植物行[[光合作用|光合作用]]時會產生二氧化碳，從而移除大氣中的碳，但進行呼吸作用時也會釋放部分二氧化碳至大氣中。只有當樹林茂盛滋長，把碳儲存於植物細胞中，才算真正移除大氣中的碳。而木材腐爛或燃燒都會讓儲存其中的碳釋放到大氣中。碳的固存主要來自於木材積聚，但樹木根部周圍共生的真菌系統同樣可以儲存大量的碳，哪怕樹木死亡、腐爛、被採伐或焚燒，碳依然被儲存於地底。<ref>{{Cite journal |last1=Clemmensen |first1=K. E. |last2=Bahr |first2=A. |last3=Ovaskainen |first3=O. |last4=Dahlberg |first4=A. |last5=Ekblad |first5=A. |last6=Wallander |first6=H. |last7=Stenlid |first7=J. |last8=Finlay |first8=R. D. |last9=Wardle |first9=D. A. |last10=Lindahl |first10=B. D. |year=2013 |title=Roots and Associated Fungi Drive Long-Term Carbon Sequestration in Boreal Forest |journal=Science |volume=339 |issue=6127 |pages=1615–8 |bibcode=2013Sci...339.1615C |doi=10.1126/science.1231923 |pmid=23539604 |s2cid=206546212}}</ref>另一種森林固碳的方式是採伐木材並製成可長久使用的產品，同時種植新樹延續生態。<ref>Prentice, I.C. [http://www.grida.no/CLIMATE/IPCC_TAR/wg1/pdf/TAR-03.PDF "The Carbon Cycle and Atmospheric Carbon Dioxide"] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090804173907/http://www.grida.no/climate/ipcc_tar/wg1/pdf/TAR-03.pdf|date=4 August 2009}}. IPCC</ref>砍伐森林也可能釋放土壤中儲存的碳。依照環境狀況不同，森林既是碳匯源也是淨排源。樹木長成後吸收二氧化碳的能力會下降，<ref>{{Cite web|title=什麼是碳匯、碳驗證？一篇文帶你看懂「森林碳權」價值，多數人都搞不清楚|url=https://www.storm.mg/lifestyle/3912891?page=1|access-date=2022-06-01|date=2021-09-05|publisher=風傳媒}}</ref>所以成熟森林的二氧化碳淨匯存及淨排放功用也會此消彼長地交替（參閱[[碳匯|碳匯]]和[[碳循環|碳循環]]）。
[[File:Manantenina_bushfire.jpg|缩略图]]
森林砍伐區的土地升溫更快、溫度更高，加速局部上升氣流，促進雲層形成，產生更多降雨。<ref>[http://www.nasa.gov/home/hqnews/2004/jun/HQ_04183_deforestation.html NASA Data Shows Deforestation Affects Climate In The Amazon]. NASA News. 9 June 2004.</ref>但是地球物理流體動力學實驗室用來研究熱帶森林砍伐的遠程響應模型顯示，整個熱帶地區的大氣溫度普遍呈現溫和升高的狀況。模型預測對流層700至150 毫巴的升溫小於0.2°C。熱帶地區以外的區域則沒有明顯變化。儘管模型顯示如此，實際情況可能不同，因為模型或許有錯，結果尚未確定。<ref>{{cite journal |last1=Findell |first1=Kirsten L. |last2=Knutson |first2=Thomas R. |last3=Milly |first3=P. C. D. |year=2006 |title=Weak Simulated Extratropical Responses to Complete Tropical Deforestation |journal=Journal of Climate |volume=19 |issue=12 |pages=2835–2850 |bibcode=2006JCli...19.2835F |citeseerx=10.1.1.143.9090 |doi=10.1175/JCLI3737.1}}</ref>無論如何，砍伐森林確實會干擾氣流、水汽和太陽能吸收，對當地氣象和全球氣候都有顯著影響。<ref>{{Cite web|title=Deforestation And Forest Degradation|url=https://www.insightsonindia.com/environment/environment-degradation-and-issues/deforestation-and-forest-degradation/|access-date=2022-02-26|website=INSIGHTSIAS|language=en-US}}</ref>

==== REDD和REDD+ ====
「減少毀林及森林環境劣化造成的溫室氣體排放計畫」（[https://www.un-redd.org/ REDD]）已成為現行氣候政策的備援新力量。概念是提供經濟補償以減少因砍伐森林及森林退化產生的溫室氣體排放。<ref>{{cite web|title=Why are we seeing "REDD"?|url=http://www.iddri.org/Publications/Collections/Analyses/Why-are-we-seeing-REDD|access-date=14 November 2016|publisher=Institute for Sustainable Development and International Relations|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20071225042425/http://www.iddri.org/Publications/Collections/Analyses/Why-are-we-seeing-REDD|archive-date=25 December 2007|author1=Wertz-Kanounnikoff, Sheila|first2=Rubio|last2=Alvarado|first3=Laura|last3=Ximena|url-status=dead}}</ref>在[[排放权交易|排放權交易]]系統中，污染者必須支付許可證費用以獲得污染物（即二氧化碳）的排放權，REDD算是這種交易系統的替代方案。

REDD+是UNFCCC締約方自願議定的方案，用以減緩氣候變遷，載明於《巴黎氣候協定》第5條，在REDD基礎上增加森林復育與永續森林管理的理念，並支持發展中國家將其國家自主貢獻（NDCs）轉化為實際的森林保護行動。<ref name=":02">{{Cite journal |author=柳婉郁、林國慶 |year=2012 |title=REDD緣起與運作機制之分析 |url=https://www.forest.gov.tw/MagazineFile.aspx?fno=6042 |journal=台灣林業 |volume=38 |page=15-19}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|title=Reducing emissions from deforestation and forest degradation|url=https://www.unep.org/explore-topics/climate-action/what-we-do/redd|access-date=2022-06-01|publisher=UNEP|language=en}}</ref>

==== 供氧誤解 ====
[[File:SouthEast_Asia_fires_Oct_2006.jpg|缩略图]]
大眾普遍認為熱帶雨林提供世上相當大量的氧氣，<ref name="timesonline.co.uk">{{Cite news|url=http://www.timesonline.co.uk/tol/news/article664544.ece|title=How can you save the rain forest. 8 October 2006. Frank Field|location=London|work=The Times|date=8 October 2006|access-date=1 April 2010}}</ref>但目前科學家認為熱帶雨林供給大氣的淨氧量並不多，而森林砍伐對大氣氧氣含量的影響也很小。<ref>Broeker, Wallace S. (2006). [http://www.columbia.edu/cu/21stC/issue-2.1/broecker.htm "Breathing easy: Et tu, O<sub>2</sub>".] Columbia University</ref><ref>{{Cite journal |last1=Moran |first1=Emilio F. |year=1993 |title=Deforestation and land use in the Brazilian Amazon |journal=Human Ecology |volume=21 |pages=1–21 |doi=10.1007/BF00890069 |s2cid=153481315}}</ref>不過燃燒木材及[[刀耕火種|刀耕火種]]都會釋放大量二氧化碳而導致全球變暖。<ref name="Fearnidel" />科學家說熱帶森林砍伐每年釋放15億噸碳至大氣中。<ref name="ReferenceC">{{cite journal |last1=Defries |first1=Ruth |last2=Achard |first2=Frédéric |last3=Brown |first3=Sandra |last4=Herold |first4=Martin |last5=Murdiyarso |first5=Daniel |last6=Schlamadinger |first6=Bernhard |last7=De Souza |first7=Carlos |year=2007 |title=Earth observations for estimating greenhouse gas emissions from deforestation in developing countries |url=http://www.gofc-gold.uni-jena.de/documents/other/EO_for_GHG_emissions.pdf |url-status=dead |journal=Environmental Science Policy |volume=10 |issue=4 |pages=385–394 |doi=10.1016/j.envsci.2007.01.010 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120118225748/http://www.gofc-gold.uni-jena.de/documents/other/EO_for_GHG_emissions.pdf |archive-date=18 January 2012}}</ref>

=== [[水文学|水文]] ===
[[File:Madagascar_highland_plateau.jpg|缩略图]]
森林砍伐也會影響水循環。樹木根部吸取[[地下水|地下水]]並將水汽釋放到大氣中。森林消失，就沒有樹木來蒸散水分，導致氣候更加乾燥。砍伐森林也減少了土壤含水量及地下水中，土壤乾涸又導致樹木可汲取的水分變少，<ref>{{cite web|title=Underlying Causes of Deforestation|url=http://www.wrm.org.uy/deforestation/UNreport.html|work=UN Secretary-General’s Report|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20010411092448/http://wrm.org.uy/deforestation/UNreport.html|archive-date=11 April 2001|url-status=dead}}</ref>使土壤凝聚力下降，造成[[土壤侵蝕|土壤侵蝕]]、洪水和[[山崩|山崩]]。<ref>{{cite web|title=Deforestation and Landslides in Southwestern Washington|url=https://people.uwec.edu/jolhm/eh2/rogge/index.htm|author=Rogge, Daniel|work=University of Wisconsin-Eau Claire}}</ref><ref>[http://news.bbc.co.uk/1/hi/world/asia-pacific/413717.stm China's floods: Is deforestation to blame?] BBC News. 6 August 1999.</ref>

森林覆蓋率降低也會減損地表攔截、保留和蒸散降水的功能。砍伐區無法收集降水，然後滲透至地下水系統，反而變成[[地表逕流|地表逕流]]，其流動速度比地下逕流快得多。森林蒸散作用可以讓大部分降水直接回到大氣中。反之，森林砍伐區幾乎所有降水都會變成逕流而流失，<ref>Raven, P. H. and Berg, L. R. (2006) ''Environment'', 5th ed, John Wiley & Sons. p. 406. {{ISBN|0471704385}}.</ref>而地表水快速流動更容易造成[[暴洪|山洪暴發]]和局部洪水氾濫。砍伐森林會減少[[蒸發散|蒸散]]而降低大氣水分，在某些情況下會影響森林砍伐區下風處的降水量，因為水不是循環降在下風處森林，而是成為地表逕流直接流向海洋。根據研究指出，1950至1980年中國華北及西北的森林砍伐區，年平均降水量減少了三分之一。<ref>{{Cite book|title=The Economic Costs of China's Environmental Degradation: Project on Environmental Scarcities, State Capacity, and Civil Violence, a Joint Project of the University of Toronto and the American Academy of Arts and Sciences|chapter-url=http://www.library.utoronto.ca/pcs/state/chinaeco/forest.htm|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20091230071928/http://www.library.utoronto.ca/pcs/state/chinaeco/forest.htm|url-status=dead|archive-date=30 December 2009|publisher=Committee on Internat. Security Studies, American Acad. of Arts and Sciences|date=1 January 1998|first=Wang|last=Hongchang|chapter=Deforestation and Desiccation in China A Preliminary Study|editor-last=Schwartz|editor-first=Jonathan Matthew}}</ref>

樹木和植物普遍來說都會強烈影響水循環：<ref name=":13">{{Cite book|title=Fundamental Concept in Environmental Studies|last=Mishra|first=D.D.|publisher=S. Chand Publishing|year=2010|isbn=978-8121929370|pages=14–15}}</ref>

* 樹冠可以攔截部分降水，然後蒸發回大氣（樹冠攔截）；
* [[凋落物|枯枝落葉]]、樹枝及樹幹可以減緩地表逕流；
* 樹根在土壤中形成的大孔隙可以增加水的滲透量；
* 有助於陸地蒸散作用來平衡土壤含水量；
* 植物凋落物和其他有機殘留物會改變土壤特性而影響儲水能力；
* 根部吸收的水分有99%輸送到葉子，葉子行蒸散作用可調節大氣濕度。<ref>[http://www.ag.ndsu.edu/pubs/ageng/irrigate/eb66w.htm "Soil, Water and Plant Characteristics Important to Irrigation".] North Dakota State University.</ref>

因此，樹木存亡會直接改變地表、土壤、地下水或大氣中的水量，反過來又影響地表侵蝕率以及供生態系統運作或人類利用的水資源。在低地平原砍伐森林使雲層形成和降雨都轉移到更高海拔地區。<ref>{{cite journal |last1=Ray |first1=Deepak K. |last2=Nair |first2=Udaysankar S. |last3=Lawton |first3=Robert O. |last4=Welch |first4=Ronald M. |last5=Pielke |first5=Roger A. |date=2006 |title=Impact of land use on Costa Rican tropical montane cloud forests: Sensitivity of orographic cloud formation to deforestation in the plains |journal=Journal of Geophysical Research |volume=111 |issue=D2 |pages=D02108 |bibcode=2006JGRD..111.2108R |doi=10.1029/2005JD006096}}</ref>平常大間歇大量降雨的情況下，森林還不至於造成洪水，但如果土壤涵養量經常處於近飽和狀態，一旦超出臨界點，後果不堪設想。

地球上大約30%的淡水來自於熱帶雨林。<ref name="timesonline.co.uk" />

砍伐森林破壞了正常氣候模式，造成更熱更乾燥的天氣，加劇乾旱、荒漠化、作物歉收、極地冰蓋融化、海岸洪水和主要植被變遷。<ref>{{Cite web|title=Deforestation as a major threat {{!}} Daily Sun {{!}}|url=https://www.daily-sun.com/printversion/details/465873/Deforestation-as-a-major-threat|access-date=2022-02-26|last=sun|first=daily|website=daily sun|language=en}}</ref>

=== 土壤 ===
[[File:Erp_-_20111006_(6).jpg|缩略图]]
原始林的土壤流失率最低，因為地表覆蓋了許多枯枝落葉。森林砍伐會降低枯枝落葉的覆蓋量，也就減少土壤抵抗地表逕流的保護力，增加土壤流失，<ref>{{Cite book|title=Soil Erosion and Conservation|last=Morgan|first=R.P.C|publisher=John Wiley & Sons|year=2009|isbn=9781405144674|pages=343}}</ref>流失率約為每平方公里1.6～2公噸，<ref>{{Cite web|title=森林砍伐嚴重 土壤流失增百倍每公頃160噸土石流|url=https://e-info.org.tw/node/43585|access-date=2022-06-06|author=中廣新聞網|date=2009-06-03|publisher=環境資訊中心}}</ref><ref name="Homestead">{{Cite book|title=21st Century Homestead: Sustainable Agriculture III: Agricultural Practices|last=Henkel|first=Marlon|date=22 February 2015|publisher=Lulu.com|isbn=9781312939752|pages=110}}{{self-published source|date=February 2020}}</ref>對於熱帶雨林過度淋溶的土壤更是雪上加霜。林業經營過程不可免的林道開發和機械化設備都加劇土壤侵蝕。

中國黃土高原經年的森林砍伐導致水土流失；使山谷形同解衣卸甲。地表水流含土量上升除了導致黃河更加氾濫也使河水顏色格外的黃。<ref name="Homestead" />

土壤侵蝕情況惡化並不總是來自森林砍伐，瞧瞧美國西南地區便可一望而知，這裡樹林灌木所造成的草地荒蕪，更勝於砍掉樹木帶來的土壤流失。<ref name="Homestead" />

但是大致說來，樹木強化土壤，樹木根系緊抓土壤基岩可起保護作用。樹木被砍伐的地區較容易發生[[山崩|山體滑坡]]。<ref name=":13" />

=== 生物多樣性 ===
[[File:Illegal_export_of_rosewood_001.jpg|缩略图]]被盜伐的紫酸枝木（''Dalbergia maritima''）]]
森林砍伐的結果就人類看來是[[生物多樣性|生物多樣性]]減少了些，<ref>Nilsson, Sten (March 2001). [http://www.actionbioscience.org/environment/nilsson.html Do We Have Enough Forests?] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190607205907/http://www.actionbioscience.org/environment/nilsson.html|date=7 June 2019}}, American Institute of Biological Sciences.</ref>但是對於地球而言，大自然許多物種就此滅絕。<ref name=":4" /><ref>{{cite news|last=Lewis|first=Sophie|date=September 9, 2020|title=Animal populations worldwide have declined by almost 70% in just 50 years, new report says|url=https://www.cbsnews.com/news/biodiversity-endangered-species-animal-population-decline-world-wildlife-fund-report-2020-09-09/|work=[[CBS_News|CBS News]]|access-date=September 10, 2020|quote="The report points to land-use change — in particular, the destruction of habitats like rainforests for farming — as the key driver for loss of biodiversity, accounting for more than half of the loss in Europe, Central Asia, North America, Latin America and the Caribbean."}}</ref>清除或破壞森林覆蓋區域會減少豐富生態使得整體環境退化。<ref name="r12" />

平心而論，自然因素造成的森林破壞，也會造成生物多樣性危機，例如美國1980年代幾場大火與火山爆發，破壞了數萬公頃的成熟花旗松林，加上伐木業興盛，導致北美斑點梟幾乎滅絕。值此同時，老熟森林不免面臨生老病死，並將原本佔據的區域讓位給其他樹種，形成新的極盛相森林，例如高地花旗松林被鐵杉-側柏林取代，影響到斑點梟的生存。只不過人為伐林的全面與劇烈，使許多物種來不及適應而滅絕。<ref>{{Cite book|title=樹，擁抱了全世界|last=大衛‧鈴木（David Suzuki）；偉恩‧葛拉帝（Wayne Grady）|publisher=貓頭鷹|year=2018|isbn=978-986-262-353-4|location=台北|pages=234-235, 243-244|edition=三版}}</ref>

森林孕育各式各樣的生物，也可供野生動物棲息，<ref>[https://www.sciencedaily.com/releases/2007/08/070808132022.htm Rainforest Biodiversity Shows Differing Patterns], ScienceDaily, 14 August 2007.</ref>還滋養了藥用植物。<ref>{{cite web|title=Medicine from the rainforest|url=http://www.bmbf.de/en/12484.php|work=Research for Biodiversity Editorial Office|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20081206015033/http://www.bmbf.de/en/12484.php|archive-date=6 December 2008|url-status=dead}}</ref>森林化育的[[群落生境|生物群落]]是新藥不可替代的來源（如紫杉醇），砍伐森林同時也不可逆地破壞了[[遺傳|遺傳]]變異（如植物抗性）。<ref>[http://www.bio-medicine.org/biology-news-1/Single-largest-biodiversity-survey-says-primary-rainforest-is-irreplaceable-1218-1/ Single-largest biodiversity survey says primary rainforest is irreplaceable] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090814233654/http://www.bio-medicine.org/biology-news-1/Single-largest-biodiversity-survey-says-primary-rainforest-is-irreplaceable-1218-1/|date=14 August 2009}}, Bio-Medicine, 14 November 2007.</ref>

因為熱帶雨林是地球上最多樣化的生態系統，<ref>[https://web.archive.org/web/20090302154517/http://www.bbc.co.uk/schools/gcsebitesize/geography/ecosystems/ecosystemsrainforestrev1.shtml Tropical rainforests – The tropical rainforest], BBC</ref><ref>[https://web.archive.org/web/20000302033338/http://library.thinkquest.org/11353/trforest.htm Tropical Rain Forest]. thinkquest.org</ref>世上已知的生物種類有80%生存在熱帶雨林中，<ref>[https://www.reuters.com/article/us-philippines-biodiversity-idUSMAN18800220080620 U.N. calls on Asian nations to end deforestation] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150924134044/http://www.reuters.com/article/2008/06/20/us-philippines-biodiversity-idUSMAN18800220080620|date=24 September 2015}}, Reuters, 20 June 2008.</ref><ref>{{Cite web|title=Facts and information on the Amazon Rainforest|url=http://www.rain-tree.com/facts.htm|website=www.rain-tree.com}}</ref>清除或破壞這麼具指標意義的森林，對生態多樣性和環境<ref>[https://www.bbc.co.uk/schools/gcsebitesize/geography/ecosystems/ecosystemsrainforestrev4.shtml Tropical rainforests – Rainforest water and nutrient cycles] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090213160024/http://www.bbc.co.uk/schools/gcsebitesize/geography/ecosystems/ecosystemsrainforestrev4.shtml|date=13 February 2009}}, BBC</ref>所造成的損害可想而知。<ref name=":4" /><ref>Butler, Rhett A. (2 July 2007) [http://news.mongabay.com/2007/0702-gardner.html Primary rainforest richer in species than plantations, secondary forests], mongabay.com,</ref>巴西[[朗多尼亚州|朗多尼亞州]]的研究顯示，砍伐森林也就破壞了那些促進養分循環、清潔水源、去除污染物的微生物群。<ref name="ro">{{cite web|title=Deforestation in the Amazon Affects Microbial Life As Well As Ecosystems|url=http://www.redorbit.com/news/science/1112753888/amazon-deforestation-microbial-communities-122512/|access-date=12 March 2013|last=Flowers|first=April|work=Science News|publisher=Redorbit.com|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130502223155/http://www.redorbit.com/news/science/1112753888/amazon-deforestation-microbial-communities-122512/|archive-date=2 May 2013|url-status=dead}}</ref>

跟據統計，雨林砍伐每一天都造成137種植物、動物及昆蟲物種滅絕，相當於每年50,000種。<ref name="rain-tree.com">[http://www.rain-tree.com/facts.htm Rainforest Facts]. Rain-tree.com (20 March 2010). Retrieved 29 August 2010.</ref>更有人說砍伐熱帶雨林就是在進行活生生的[[全新世滅絕事件|全新世大滅絕]]。<ref>Leakey, Richard and Roger Lewin, 1996, ''The Sixth Extinction : Patterns of Life and the Future of Humankind'', Anchor, {{ISBN|0-385-46809-1}}.</ref><ref>[https://www.independent.co.uk/environment/the-great-rainforest-tragedy-542135.html The great rainforest tragedy] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110912071556/http://www.independent.co.uk/environment/the-great-rainforest-tragedy-542135.html|date=12 September 2011}}, The Independent, 28 June 2003.</ref>其他地區因森林砍伐所導致的生物滅絕率比較低，哺乳動物和鳥類每個分支每年大約都減少1個物種，推算所有類別每年大約有23,000個物種絕跡。東南亞超過40%的動、植物物種預計在21世紀滅絕。<ref>[https://www.newscientist.com/channel/life/endangered-species/dn3973 Biodiversity wipeout facing South East Asia], New Scientist, 23 July 2003.</ref>1995年某項研究數據則挑戰這一類預測，因為數據顯示雖然東南亞地區大部分原始森林已經變成單一作物種植區，但瀕臨滅絕的物種卻很少，樹木群仍然廣泛而穩定地生長。<ref name="ReferenceB">{{cite journal |last1=Pimm |first1=S. L. |last2=Russell |first2=G. J. |last3=Gittleman |first3=J. L. |last4=Brooks |first4=T. M. |year=1995 |title=The Future of Biodiversity |journal=Science |volume=269 |issue=5222 |pages=347–350 |bibcode=1995Sci...269..347P |doi=10.1126/science.269.5222.347 |pmid=17841251 |s2cid=35154695}}</ref>

目前對於物種滅絕過程的科學知識，尚不足以準確預測森林砍伐對生物多樣性造成的影響。<ref>{{cite journal |last1=Pimm |first1=S. L. |last2=Russell |first2=G. J. |last3=Gittleman |first3=J. L. |last4=Brooks |first4=T. M. |year=1995 |title=The future of biodiversity |journal=Science |volume=269 |issue=5222 |pages=347–50 |bibcode=1995Sci...269..347P |doi=10.1126/science.269.5222.347 |pmid=17841251 |s2cid=35154695}}</ref>關於林業造成生物多樣性喪失的大多數預測都是基於物種區域模型，預設了森林面積減少，物種多樣性將同樣下降。但是這類模型很多已被證明是錯誤的，[[棲息地破壞|失去棲息地]]不一定會導致大規模的物種滅絕。<ref name="ReferenceA">{{cite book|author1=Whitmore, Timothy Charles|author2=Sayer, Jeffrey|author3=International Union for Conservation of Nature and Natural Resources. General Assembly|author4=IUCN Forest Conservation Programme|title=Tropical deforestation and species extinction|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=Et4opq8dn4MC|date=15 February 1992|publisher=Springer|isbn=978-0-412-45520-9}}</ref>物種區域模型高估了實際砍伐區中受威脅的物種數量，於是也高估了全森林區中所有受威脅的物種數量。<ref name="ReferenceB" />

雖然如此，最近對巴西亞馬遜地區的研究指出，就算到現在為止物種還沒有消失，但預測未來40年內物種終究會滅絕的機率高達90%。<ref>{{cite web|title=More extinctions expected in Amazon|url=http://news.discovery.com/earth/amazon-extinctions-to-come-120712.html|access-date=13 July 2012|date=12 July 2012|last=Sohn|first=Emily|work=Discovery|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20121107175209/http://news.discovery.com/earth/amazon-extinctions-to-come-120712.html|archive-date=7 November 2012|url-status=dead}}</ref>

== 健康影響 ==

=== 公共衛生的脈絡 ===
森林退化及消失會破壞大自然平衡。<ref name=":5" />森林砍伐所造成的大量動植物物種滅絕，確實導致疾病增加<ref name="CHGE">[http://www.chgeharvard.org/topic/biodiversity-and-infectious-diseases Biodiversity and Infectious Diseases] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160512175341/http://www.chgeharvard.org/topic/biodiversity-and-infectious-diseases|date=12 May 2016}}, Center for Health and the Global Environment, [[Harvard_T.H._Chan_School_of_Public_Health|Harvard T.H. Chan School of Public Health]], Harvard University (last accessed 15 May 2017.</ref>，提高[[人畜共通傳染病|人畜共通病]]的風險。<ref name=":5" /><ref>{{Cite web|title=UN Decade on Ecosystem Restoration|url=https://www.decadeonrestoration.org/}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|title=New UN Decade on Ecosystem Restoration offers unparalleled opportunity for job creation, food security and addressing climate change|url=http://www.fao.org/news/story/en/item/1182090/icode/}}</ref><ref>{{Cite book|url=https://doi.org/10.4060/ca9456en|title=Global emergence of infectious diseases: links with wild meat consumption, ecosystem disruption, habitat degradation and biodiversity loss|publisher=FAO|year=2020|isbn=978-92-5-132818-7|location=Rome|doi=10.4060/ca9456en|s2cid=240645073}}</ref>砍伐森林還為非本地物種繁殖大開方便之門，例如某些蝸牛類型造成[[血吸虫病|血吸蟲病]]的病例增加。<ref name="CHGE" /><ref>{{Cite journal |last1=Moslemi |first1=Jennifer M. |last2=Snider |first2=Sunny B. |last3=MacNeill |first3=Keeley |last4=Gilliam |first4=James F. |last5=Flecker |first5=Alexander S. |year=2012 |title=Impacts of an Invasive Snail |journal=PLOS ONE |volume=7 |issue=6 |pages=e38806 |bibcode=2012PLoSO...738806M |doi=10.1371/journal.pone.0038806 |pmc=3382606 |pmid=22761706 |doi-access=free}}</ref>

森林相關人畜共通病有[[疟疾|瘧疾]]、[[恰加斯病|南美錐蟲病]]（也稱為美洲錐蟲病）、[[非洲人类锥虫病|非洲錐蟲病]]（昏睡病）、[[利什曼病|利什曼病]]、[[莱姆病|萊姆病]]、[[人類免疫缺陷病毒|人類免疫缺乏病毒]]和[[埃博拉出血热|伊波拉出血熱]]。<ref name=":5" />大多數會影響人類的新傳染病都是人畜共通病，例如造成COVID-19大流行的[[嚴重急性呼吸系統綜合症冠狀病毒2型|SARS-CoV2病毒]]。<ref>{{Cite web|title=新冠病毒從何而來？ 專家：動物傳人疾病的共通點在「森林砍伐」|url=https://e-info.org.tw/node/225465|access-date=2020-06-08|author=姜唯，林大利|date=2020-07-06|publisher=環境資訊中心}}</ref>這些疾病可能與森林面積變化及人口侵入森林地區導致棲地喪失有關，因為這兩種狀況都會讓人類頻繁接觸野生動物。<ref name=":5" />

世界各地的森林砍伐方興未艾，相關疾病爆發狀況也同步增加。馬來西亞有數千英畝伐除森林土地用於興建養豬場，增加了[[立百病毒|立百病毒]]造成之人畜共通病。<ref>[http://thebulletin.org/deforestation-and-emerging-diseases Deforestation and emerging diseases | Bulletin of the Atomic Scientists]. Thebulletin.org (15 February 2011). Retrieved 13 November 2016.</ref>[[肯尼亚|肯亞]]的森林砍伐也促使瘧疾病例增加，也是目前該國[[发病率|發病率]]和[[死亡率|死亡率]]的升高主因。<ref>[http://www.african-politics.com/tag/environmental-impact-of-deforestation-in-kenya/ African Politics Portal | Tag Archive | Environmental impact of deforestation in Kenya] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160413022408/http://www.african-politics.com/tag/environmental-impact-of-deforestation-in-kenya/|date=13 April 2016}}. African-politics.com (28 May 2009). Retrieved 13 November 2016.</ref><ref>[http://kff.org/news-summary/2014-kenya-economic-survey-marks-malaria-as-countrys-leading-cause-of-death/ 2014 Kenya Economic Survey Marks Malaria As Country’s Leading Cause Of Death | The Henry J. Kaiser Family Foundation]. Kff.org (1 May 2014). Retrieved 13 November 2016.</ref>《[[美國經濟評論|美國經濟評論]]》2017年的研究發現，森林砍伐的確增加了[[奈及利亞|奈及利亞]]的瘧疾發病率。<ref>{{Cite journal |last1=Julia |first1=Berazneva |last2=S. |first2=Byker, Tanya |date=1 May 2017 |title=Does Forest Loss Increase Human Disease? Evidence from Nigeria |journal=American Economic Review |language=en |volume=107 |issue=5 |pages=516–521 |doi=10.1257/aer.p20171132 |issn=0002-8282 |pmid=29557569}}</ref>

森林砍伐對於疾病的另一種影響方式，是疾病帶原者的遷移和散布，稱為「'''[[定殖|範圍擴展]]'''」，即宿主的範圍（以及病原體的範圍）擴展到新的地理區域。<ref>{{Cite journal |last1=Scheidt |first1=Spencer N. |last2=Hurlbert |first2=Allen H. |year=2014 |title=Range Expansion and Population Dynamics of an Invasive Species: The Eurasian Collared-Dove (''Streptopelia decaocto'') |journal=PLOS ONE |volume=9 |issue=10 |pages=e111510 |bibcode=2014PLoSO...9k1510S |doi=10.1371/journal.pone.0111510 |pmc=4213033 |pmid=25354270 |doi-access=free}}</ref>因為森林被砍伐，自然宿主和寄宿物種被迫遷移到鄰近棲息地，病原體也隨之移動，並在新棲地找到新宿主。人類和這些病原體及物種密切地接觸，難免直接或間接地遭到感染。

範圍擴展的災難案例是1998年在馬來西亞爆發的[[尼帕病毒感染|立百病毒感染]]。<ref>{{cite journal |last1=Lam |first1=Sai Kit |last2=Chua |first2=Kaw Bing |year=2002 |title=Nipah Virus Encephalitis Outbreak in Malaysia |journal=Clinical Infectious Diseases |volume=34 |pages=S48–51 |doi=10.1086/338818 |pmid=11938496 |doi-access=free}}</ref>經年的森林砍伐、乾旱和後續的火災，使尼帕病毒宿主—[[果蝠屬|果蝠]]的分佈區域及密度都發生巨大變化。<ref>{{cite web|title=Nipah Virus (NiV)|url=https://www.cdc.gov/vhf/nipah/|date=25 February 2019|publisher=cdc.gov}}</ref>砍伐森林造成果蝠原本棲息的樹木減少，只好入侵周邊果園，果園正是大量豬圈所在地。蝙蝠就近將立百病毒傳染給豬隻。豬隻雖被感染，但死亡率遠低於周遭人類，於是變成傳播病毒給人類的超級宿主，共計造成了265例[[脑炎|腦炎]]病例，其中105例死亡。這個案例揭示了森林砍伐對人類健康的重大影響。

另一個森林砍伐及人類危害棲地而導致範圍擴展的案例是巴拉圭的[[水豚|水豚]]。<ref>[http://news.mongabay.com/2010/12/deforestation-sparks-giant-rodent-invasions/ Deforestation sparks giant rodent invasions]. News.mongabay.com (15 December 2010). Retrieved 13 November 2016.</ref>這種[[啮齿动物|囓齒動物]]是多種人畜共通病的宿主，雖然水豚遷移到新棲地尚未造成人傳人疾病爆發，卻是說明森林砍伐和後續物種遷移造成[[棲息地破壞|棲息地破壞]]日益普及的範例。

目前已被廣遍接受的成熟理論描述由[[黑猩猩|黑猩猩]]所傳播的愛滋病毒至少有部分是砍伐森林所造成：不斷增長的人口創造了更多食物需求，帶動的森林砍伐開墾了新區域，獵人捕獲大量靈長類動物當成[[丛林肉|叢林肉]]食用，被認為是愛滋病毒的起源。<ref name="CHGE" />

印尼的研究發現，在熱帶雨林砍伐區的戶外工作者大多有認知及記憶障礙的經驗，似乎因為暴露在高溫之下所致；相反地，在天然熱帶雨林區的戶外工作者則少有上述狀況，樹木保護他們免於傷害。<ref>{{Cite journal |last1=Masuda |first1=Yuta J. |last2=Garg |first2=Teevrat |last3=Anggraeni |first3=Ike |last4=Wolff |first4=Nicholas H. |last5=Ebi |first5=Kristie |last6=Game |first6=Edward T. |last7=Krenz |first7=Jennifer |last8=Spector |first8=June T. |year=2020 |title=Heat exposure from tropical deforestation decreases cognitive performance of rural workers: An experimental study |url=https://www.researchgate.net/publication/344292348 |journal=Environmental Research Letters |volume=15 |issue=12 |page=124015 |bibcode=2020ERL....15l4015M |doi=10.1088/1748-9326/abb96c |doi-access=free}}</ref>森林砍伐減少了熱帶地區數百萬人的安全工作時間，尤其是從事大量戶外勞動的人。全球持續暖化和森林不斷消失預計將會放大這些效應，更加減少弱勢族群的工作時間。<ref>{{Cite web|title=Deforestation making outdoor work unsafe for millions, says study|url=https://www.theguardian.com/environment/2021/dec/17/deforestation-making-outdoor-work-unsafe-for-millions-says-study|access-date=2021-12-18|date=2021-12-17|last=Quaglia|first=Sofia|website=The Guardian|language=en|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211217163119/https://www.theguardian.com/environment/2021/dec/17/deforestation-making-outdoor-work-unsafe-for-millions-says-study|archive-date=17 December 2021|url-status=live}}</ref>

=== 概觀 ===
據《[[世界經濟論壇|世界經濟論壇]]》研究，31%新興疾病與森林砍伐有關。<ref>{{cite book|title=Outbreak Readiness and Business Impact Protecting Lives and Livelihoods across the Global Economy|date=January 2019|publisher=World Economic Forum, Harvard Global Health Institute|page=7|url=http://www3.weforum.org/docs/WEF%20HGHI_Outbreak_Readiness_Business_Impact.pdf|access-date=12 March 2020}}</ref>

根據美國疾病控制與預防中心（CDC）的數據，人類有75%的新興疾病來自動物。病例增加可能與棲地減少及生物多樣性喪失有關，科學家因此創建新的學科—行星健康（planetary health），假定生態系統健康和人類健康息息相關並加以研究。<ref name="tipiceberg">{{Cite news|last=Vidal|first=John|url=https://www.theguardian.com/environment/2020/mar/18/tip-of-the-iceberg-is-our-destruction-of-nature-responsible-for-covid-19-aoe|title='Tip of the iceberg': is our destruction of nature responsible for Covid-19?|date=2020-03-18|work=The Guardian|access-date=2020-03-18|language=en-GB|issn=0261-3077}}</ref>2015年[[洛克菲勒基金會|洛克菲勒基金會]]和《[[柳葉刀_(雜誌)|刺胳針]]》醫學期刊共同推出「洛克菲勒基金會暨《刺胳針》行星健康委員會」的概念。<ref name="Lancet2015">{{cite journal |date=2015-11-14 |title=Safeguarding human health in the Anthropocene epoch: report of The Rockefeller Foundation–Lancet Commission on planetary health |url=http://www.thelancet.com/journals/lancet/article/PIIS0140-6736(15)60901-1/fulltext |journal=The Lancet |access-date=2016-10-05}}</ref>

自1980年起，人類新傳染病數量每十年就增加三倍以上。根據美國和澳大利亞科學家的重要研究，生態系統退化會增加新傳染病爆發風險。近幾十年來，動物傳染給人類的疾病包括艾滋病毒、埃博拉病毒、[[禽流感|禽流感]]、[[豬流感|豬流感]]，COVID-19可能也是。<ref name="Deutsche Welle">{{cite news|last1=Shield|first1=Charli|title=Coronavirus Pandemic Linked to Destruction of Wildlife and World's Ecosystems|url=https://www.dw.com/en/coronavirus-pandemic-linked-to-destruction-of-wildlife-and-worlds-ecosystems/a-53078480|access-date=16 April 2020|agency=[[Deutsche_Welle|Deutsche Welle]]|date=16 April 2020}}</ref>

2016年聯合國環境規劃署發布了《[https://wedocs.unep.org/rest/bitstreams/e85b77cb-7ec3-4d4b-a654-6fa0f9e5f0dd/retrieve UNEP 2016年前沿報告：全球環境新興問題]》。報告第二章專門討論人畜共通病，指出森林砍伐、氣候變化和[[畜牧业|畜牧業]]是此類疾病風險升高的主因，並提及每四個月就會發現一種新的人畜共通病。截至2016年所爆發的疫情已經造成了數十億美元的生命財產損失，如果傳染病在未來大流行，損失將高達數萬億美元。<ref name=":52">{{cite book|title=UNEP Frontiers 2016 Report: Emerging Issues of Environmental Concern|date=2016|publisher=United Nations Environment Programme|location=Nairoby|isbn=978-92-807-3553-6|pages=18–32|url=https://environmentlive.unep.org/media/docs/assessments/UNEP_Frontiers_2016_report_emerging_issues_of_environmental_concern.pdf|access-date=1 May 2020}} [[File:CC-BY_icon.svg|50x50像素]] Text was copied from this source, which is available under a [[creativecommons:by/4.0/|Creative Commons Attribution 4.0 International License]]</ref>

